						               													<description>In Campfire, each player is attempting to build three campsites before any other player. The game focuses on building up campsites while using camp wrecking critters to prevent your opponents from finishing first. Campfire is a family-friendly card game designed to be quick to learn for players of all ages.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players draw from a shared deck full of cards to help build their camp, wreck other camps, and alter game play. Taking turns, players draw a card, play cards on the table in front of them in three camps, and play camp wreckers and game changer cards to the discard. At the end of a player's turn, they must discard one card from their hand (if they have any cards left) and replenish their hand. Play continues counter-clockwise. Discards are shuffled to replenish the deck when it runs out.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Campsites consist of two comfort cards, two food cards, and are completed with a campfire card that must be the last card played on a campsite. Cards are stacked in the order they are played and only the top card of any campsite is vulnerable to camp wrecking attacks.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to complete three camps wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
